==English==
===Etymology===
First attested [[w:1857|1857]], from [[Modern Latin]] [[onco-]] "tumor," from {{Gr.}} [[onkos]] "lump, mass, bulk" + [[-logy]] "study of," from [[Gr.]] [[logia]], from [[logos]], "word."

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-oncology.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
'''oncology''' {{wikipedia}}
#The branch of [[medicine]] concerned with [[tumor]]s, including study of their [[development]], [[diagnosis]], [[treatment]], and [[prevention]].

